{"parentUuid":"2c4ad20f-4804-459d-b235-c8f33ecd6304","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"16bbafd3-c19b-47db-9608-c29cc427596a","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PRTRFQ7k4Dq93XMh4GWqYD","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Skills\n2\t\n3\tCross-agent skills and commands powered by Entire.\n4\t\n5\tThis repo is a shared skill collection for:\n6\t\n7\t- Codex\n8\t- Claude\n9\t- OpenCode\n10\t- Cursor\n11\t- Gemini\n12\t\n13\t## Skills\n14\t\n15\t### `session-handoff`\n16\t\n17\tReads Entire session metadata and helps move work from one agent to another without making the user reconstruct the context manually.\n18\t\n19\tCurrent behavior:\n20\t\n21\t- auto-detects the most recent session from `.git/entire-sessions/`\n22\t- reads the raw transcript at the path stored in session metadata\n23\t- produces a structured compaction summary (Task Overview, Current State, Important Discoveries, Next Steps, Context to Preserve) instead of dumping raw transcript lines\n24\t- surfaces unanswered questions from the previous agent for the user to answer\n25\t- supports checkpoint handoff via `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --full --no-pager`\n26\t- falls back to `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --raw-transcript --no-pager` if full output is unavailable\n27\t- resolves checkpoints from: local `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch, `.entire/settings.json` `checkpoint_remote`, or nearby local clone\n28\t- filters sessions by agent name (e.g. \"codex\", \"gemini\") when mentioned\n29\t\n30\t### `explain`\n31\t\n32\tTraces source code back to the original conversation where it was created. Use `/explain` with a function, file, or line of code to understand _why_ it exists.\n33\t\n34\tCurrent behavior:\n35\t\n36\t- identifies the commit that introduced the code via git blame/log\n37\t- reads the session transcript via `entire explain --no-pager --commit <sha>`\n38\t- works with functions, files, and individual line changes\n39\t- reports clearly when code is untracked, uncommitted, or created outside an Entire session\n40\t\n41\t### `search`\n42\t\n43\tSearches Entire checkpoint history and transcripts to find prior work by topic, repo, branch, author, or time window.\n44\t\n45\tCurrent behavior:\n46\t\n47\t- runs `entire search \"<query>\" --json` and summarizes the top matches\n48\t- supports filters: `--repo`, `--branch`, `--author`, `--date`, and inline query filters like `author:<name>`, `date:week`\n49\t- drills into a specific result with `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --full --no-pager`\n50\t- broadens searches progressively when initial results are empty (remove branch filter, widen date, simplify terms)\n51\t\n52\t## Installation\n53\t\n54\tInstall the agent that matches your workflow from its marketplace, manifest, or install-doc entrypoint:\n55\t\n56\t### Claude Code (via Plugin Marketplace)\n57\t\n58\tIn Claude Code, register the marketplace first:\n59\t\n60\t```bash\n61\t/plugin marketplace add entireio/skills\n62\t```\n63\t\n64\tThen install the plugin from this marketplace:\n65\t\n66\t```bash\n67\t/plugin install entire \n68\t```\n69\t\n70\t### Codex\n71\t\n72\tUse `plugins/entire/.codex-plugin/plugin.json`.\n73\t\n74\t### OpenCode\n75\t\n76\tUse the package-based flow in `.opencode/INSTALL.md`.\n77\t\n78\t### Cursor\n79\t\n80\tUse `.cursor-plugin/plugin.json`.\n81\t\n82\t### Gemini\n83\t\n84\t```bash\n85\tgemini extensions install https://github.com/entireio/skills\n86\t```\n87\t\n88\t## Quick Start\n89\t\n90\tNatural language examples:\n91\t\n92\t- \"hand off this session\"\n93\t- \"hand off the codex session\"\n94\t- \"pick up where codex left off\"\n95\t- \"hand off checkpoint 7b7c2be8a262\"\n96\t- `/explain parseConfig` — why does this function exist?\n97\t- `/explain src/auth.ts` — what drove this file's creation?\n98\t- \"search past work for rate limiting\"\n99\t- \"find checkpoints about the migration\"\n100\t- \"have we done this before?\"\n101\t\n102\t## Checkpoint Resolution\n103\t\n104\tCheckpoints are resolved in this order:\n105\t\n106\t1. local `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch\n107\t2. `.entire/settings.json` `checkpoint_remote`\n108\t3. nearby local clone\n109\t"}]},"uuid":"d671feb5-ec7d-4af6-9f4f-82c15b5f8e4e","timestamp":"2026-04-23T23:57:13.649Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/alisha/Projects/skills/README.md","content":"# Skills\n\nCross-agent skills and commands powered by Entire.\n\nThis repo is a shared skill collection for:\n\n- Codex\n- Claude\n- OpenCode\n- Cursor\n- Gemini\n\n## Skills\n\n### `session-handoff`\n\nReads Entire session metadata and helps move work from one agent to another without making the user reconstruct the context manually.\n\nCurrent behavior:\n\n- auto-detects the most recent session from `.git/entire-sessions/`\n- reads the raw transcript at the path stored in session metadata\n- produces a structured compaction summary (Task Overview, Current State, Important Discoveries, Next Steps, Context to Preserve) instead of dumping raw transcript lines\n- surfaces unanswered questions from the previous agent for the user to answer\n- supports checkpoint handoff via `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --full --no-pager`\n- falls back to `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --raw-transcript --no-pager` if full output is unavailable\n- resolves checkpoints from: local `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch, `.entire/settings.json` `checkpoint_remote`, or nearby local clone\n- filters sessions by agent name (e.g. \"codex\", \"gemini\") when mentioned\n\n### `explain`\n\nTraces source code back to the original conversation where it was created. Use `/explain` with a function, file, or line of code to understand _why_ it exists.\n\nCurrent behavior:\n\n- identifies the commit that introduced the code via git blame/log\n- reads the session transcript via `entire explain --no-pager --commit <sha>`\n- works with functions, files, and individual line changes\n- reports clearly when code is untracked, uncommitted, or created outside an Entire session\n\n### `search`\n\nSearches Entire checkpoint history and transcripts to find prior work by topic, repo, branch, author, or time window.\n\nCurrent behavior:\n\n- runs `entire search \"<query>\" --json` and summarizes the top matches\n- supports filters: `--repo`, `--branch`, `--author`, `--date`, and inline query filters like `author:<name>`, `date:week`\n- drills into a specific result with `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --full --no-pager`\n- broadens searches progressively when initial results are empty (remove branch filter, widen date, simplify terms)\n\n## Installation\n\nInstall the agent that matches your workflow from its marketplace, manifest, or install-doc entrypoint:\n\n### Claude Code (via Plugin Marketplace)\n\nIn Claude Code, register the marketplace first:\n\n```bash\n/plugin marketplace add entireio/skills\n```\n\nThen install the plugin from this marketplace:\n\n```bash\n/plugin install entire \n```\n\n### Codex\n\nUse `plugins/entire/.codex-plugin/plugin.json`.\n\n### OpenCode\n\nUse the package-based flow in `.opencode/INSTALL.md`.\n\n### Cursor\n\nUse `.cursor-plugin/plugin.json`.\n\n### Gemini\n\n```bash\ngemini extensions install https://github.com/entireio/skills\n```\n\n## Quick Start\n\nNatural language examples:\n\n- \"hand off this session\"\n- \"hand off the codex session\"\n- \"pick up where codex left off\"\n- \"hand off checkpoint 7b7c2be8a262\"\n- `/explain parseConfig` — why does this function exist?\n- `/explain src/auth.ts` — what drove this file's creation?\n- \"search past work for rate limiting\"\n- \"find checkpoints about the migration\"\n- \"have we done this before?\"\n\n## Checkpoint Resolution\n\nCheckpoints are resolved in this order:\n\n1. local `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch\n2. `.entire/settings.json` `checkpoint_remote`\n3. nearby local clone\n","numLines":109,"startLine":1,"totalLines":109}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"2c4ad20f-4804-459d-b235-c8f33ecd6304","userType":"external",