r that includes a `name` field and a `description` field.\n\n### Required Fields\n\n**name**: The skill identifier, using lowercase letters, numbers, and hyphens only. The readable skill name is optional—if omitted, the folder name is used.\n\n**description**: A short and objective description of what the skill does and when to use it (appears in menus), which is used by the agent to decide when to apply the skill.\n\n### Example Format\n\nThe frontmatter looks like:\n```\n--- name: my-skill description: Short description of what this skill does and when to use it. ---\n```\n\n### Key Details\n\n- At startup, the agent pre-loads the name and description of every installed skill into its system prompt.\n- The description field is how the agent chooses whether to use a skill—make it specific and natural.\n- Write descriptions in third person and include what, when, and natural trigger phrases.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"fd5bccef-d468-4216-92d4-d7b03100682e","timestamp":"2026-04-23T23:58:02.368Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"Cursor \".cursor/skills\" SKILL.md frontmatter name description","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01UUABtgTGJ4JPkrj51Rny6y","content":[{"title":".cursor/docs/cursor-skills.md at main · hutchic/.cursor","url":"https://github.com/hutchic/.cursor/blob/main/docs/cursor-skills.md"},{"title":"Cursor rules vs skills — what's the actual difference? - DEV Community","url":"https://dev.to/nedcodes/cursor-rules-vs-skills-whats-the-actual-difference-383b"},{"title":"cursor-skill-creator","url":"https://lobehub.com/skills/tech-leads-club-agent-skills-cursor-skill-creator"},{"title":"Skills Provider - FastMCP","url":"https://gofastmcp.com/servers/providers/skills"},{"title":"How Cursor Finds Skills | Agentic Thinking","url":"https://agenticthinking.ai/blog/skill-discovery/"},{"title":"SKILL.md is created when creating new cursor rules - Help - Cursor - Community Forum","ur