{"parentUuid":"42414874-f81a-458d-975c-93b96586e9e1","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"16bbafd3-c19b-47db-9608-c29cc427596a","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QjHgnGsUuXGFMfamskVwXm","type":"tool_result","content":"# Local Cursor Plugin Installation\n\n## Installation Steps\n\nTo install a Cursor plugin locally, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Copy plugin files** to `~/.cursor/plugins/<plugin-name>/`\n\n2. **Register in `~/.claude/plugins/installed_plugins.json`** with an entry like:\n   ```json\n   {\n     \"plugins\": {\n       \"plugin-name@local\": [\n         {\n           \"scope\": \"user\",\n           \"installPath\": \"/Users/you/.cursor/plugins/plugin-name\"\n         }\n       ]\n     }\n   }\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable in `~/.claude/settings.json`**:\n   ```json\n   {\n     \"enabledPlugins\": {\n       \"plugin-name@local\": true\n     }\n   }\n   ```\n\n4. **Verify third-party plugin setting** is enabled in Settings > Features\n\n## Key Points\n\n- Use **absolute paths** for `installPath`—relative paths are unreliable\n- The plugin directory structure requires `.cursor-plugin/` (not `.claude-plugin/`)\n- \"The `@local` suffix appears to signal a locally-installed plugin\"\n- Restart Cursor fully after installation; \"Reload Window sometimes works, full restart is safer\"\n\n## Common Issues\n\nThe article notes these typical problems:\n- Using `.claude-plugin/` instead of `.cursor-plugin/`\n- Installing under `~/.cursor/skills/` only (commands won't register)\n- Plugin registered but not enabled in both JSON files\n- Incomplete restart of the IDE\n\n**Note:** The article covers macOS specifically; Windows/Linux paths differ."}]},"uuid":"d7ef50f3-f2f2-43c4-8dca-28a2e99cda8b","timestamp":"2026-04-23T23:58:24.138Z","toolUseResult":{"bytes":149467,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Local Cursor Plugin Installation\n\n## Installation Steps\n\nTo install a Cursor plugin locally, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Copy plugin files** to `~/.cursor/plugins/<plugin-name>/`\n\n2. **Register in `~/.claude/plugins/installed_plugins.json`** with an entry like:\n   ```json\n   {\n     \"plugins\": {\n       \"plugin-name@local\": [\n         {\n           \"scope\": \"user\",\n           \"installPath\": \"/Users/you/.cursor/plugins/plugin-name\"\n         }\n       ]\n     }\n   }\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable in `~/.claude/settings.json`**:\n   ```json\n   {\n     \"enabledPlugins\": {\n       \"plugin-name@local\": true\n     }\n   }\n   ```\n\n4. **Verify third-party plugin setting** is enabled in Settings > Features\n\n## Key Points\n\n- Use **absolute paths** for `installPath`—relative paths are unreliable\n- The plugin directory structure requires `.cursor-plugin/` (not `.claude-plugin/`)\n- \"The `@local` suffix appears to signal a locally-installed plugin\"\n- Restart Cursor fully after installation; \"Reload Window sometimes works, full restart is safer\"\n\n## Common Issues\n\nThe article notes these typical problems:\n- Using `.claude-plugin/` instead of `.cursor-plugin/`\n- Installing under `~/.cursor/skills/` only (commands won't register)\n- Plugin registered but not enabled in both JSON files\n- Incomplete restart of the IDE\n\n**Note:** The article covers macOS specifically; Windows/Linux paths differ.","durationMs":10189,"url":"https://medium.com/@v.tajzich/how-to-write-and-test-cursor-plugins-locally-the-part-the-docs-dont-tell-you-4eee705d7f76"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"42414874-f81a-458d-975c-93b96586e9e1","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/alisha/Projects/skills","sessionId":"415c4d06-7225-447d-a197-6c6793576b63","version":"2.1.119","gitBranch":"alisha/cursor-install-bug"}
