{"parentUuid":"fdee278f-df17-42e5-ad20-fc691bf5600b","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"16bbafd3-c19b-47db-9608-c29cc427596a","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012iEDF9GYf4JqPr1VyzFqB2","type":"tool_result","content":"# Cursor Plugin Installation\n\nBased on the documentation provided:\n\n## Standard Installation\nUsers install plugins through the marketplace panel in Cursor or from the official [Cursor Marketplace](/marketplace).\n\n## Local Installation\nYes, Cursor supports local plugin testing. You can load plugins from `~/.cursor/plugins/local/`:\n\n1. Create a folder: `~/.cursor/plugins/local/my-plugin`\n2. Copy plugin files there (ensuring `.cursor-plugin/plugin.json` is at the root)\n3. Restart Cursor or run **Developer: Reload Window**\n\nFor development, you can also \"symlink your plugin repository\" for faster iteration.\n\n## Directory Structure\nThe documentation shows this plugin structure:\n```\nmy-plugin/\n├── .cursor-plugin/\n│   └── plugin.json\n├── rules/\n├── skills/\n└── mcp.json\n```\n\nHowever, the document doesn't specify the complete `~/.cursor/` layout or confirm a dedicated `~/.cursor/skills/` directory.\n\n## CLI/GitHub Installation\nThe documentation doesn't mention CLI installation or direct GitHub URL support for users. Team marketplaces can be imported via GitHub repositories, but this requires admin access to dashboard settings—not standard user-facing CLI functionality."}]},"uuid":"d0305e31-4edd-4cb7-952e-572928684b93","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:04:26.612Z","toolUseResult":{"bytes":7553,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Cursor Plugin Installation\n\nBased on the documentation provided:\n\n## Standard Installation\nUsers install plugins through the marketplace panel in Cursor or from the official [Cursor Marketplace](/marketplace).\n\n## Local Installation\nYes, Cursor supports local plugin testing. You can load plugins from `~/.cursor/plugins/local/`:\n\n1. Create a folder: `~/.cursor/plugins/local/my-plugin`\n2. Copy plugin files there (ensuring `.cursor-plugin/plugin.json` is at the root)\n3. Restart Cursor or run **Developer: Reload Window**\n\nFor development, you can also \"symlink your plugin repository\" for faster iteration.\n\n## Directory Structure\nThe documentation shows this plugin structure:\n```\nmy-plugin/\n├── .cursor-plugin/\n│   └── plugin.json\n├── rules/\n├── skills/\n└── mcp.json\n```\n\nHowever, the document doesn't specify the complete `~/.cursor/` layout or confirm a dedicated `~/.cursor/skills/` directory.\n\n## CLI/GitHub Installation\nThe documentation doesn't mention CLI installation or direct GitHub URL support for users. Team marketplaces can be imported via GitHub repositories, but this requires admin access to dashboard settings—not standard user-facing CLI functionality.","durationMs":3474,"url":"https://cursor.com/docs/plugins"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"fdee278f-df17-42e5-ad20-fc691bf5600b","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/alisha/Projects/skills","sessionId":"415c4d06-7225-447d-a197-6c6793576b63","version":"2.1.119","gitBranch":"alisha/cursor-install-bug"}
