{"parentUuid":"67f6a643-bc16-4e61-99ae-ff3dd39b25f3","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"16bbafd3-c19b-47db-9608-c29cc427596a","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TK9iCVmHezKQnScvSUhwZN","type":"tool_result","content":"# Installing Cursor Plugins Locally in 2.5+\n\nBased on the guide, here are the essential steps:\n\n## Installation Process\n\n1. **Create symlink** to the plugins directory:\n   - macOS/Linux: `ln -s /path/to/my-plugin ~/.cursor/plugins/my-plugin`\n   - Windows: `mklink /D %USERPROFILE%\\.cursor\\plugins\\my-plugin C:\\path\\to\\my-plugin`\n\n2. **Restart Cursor** to detect the newly linked plugin\n\n3. **Verify plugin appears** in the plugin list\n\n## Required Structure\n\nYour plugin directory needs a `plugin.json` manifest file defining metadata and component paths, plus directories for skills, rules, subagents, MCP servers, and hooks as applicable.\n\n## Common Issues\n\nThe guide identifies several failure points:\n\n- **Malformed plugin.json**: \"Even a small error here prevents the plugin from loading\"\n- **Incorrect file paths** in the manifest (use relative paths from plugin root)\n- **File permission problems**, particularly on macOS\n- **Caching issues** requiring full Cursor restarts\n- **Missing required fields** in the configuration\n\nThe symlink approach represents a workaround rather than official support for local development, so expect this workflow to potentially change as Cursor evolves its plugin system."}]},"uuid":"cc9a5b04-9b43-402a-a84e-e84d321bf07b","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:04:41.221Z","toolUseResult":{"bytes":136568,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Installing Cursor Plugins Locally in 2.5+\n\nBased on the guide, here are the essential steps:\n\n## Installation Process\n\n1. **Create symlink** to the plugins directory:\n   - macOS/Linux: `ln -s /path/to/my-plugin ~/.cursor/plugins/my-plugin`\n   - Windows: `mklink /D %USERPROFILE%\\.cursor\\plugins\\my-plugin C:\\path\\to\\my-plugin`\n\n2. **Restart Cursor** to detect the newly linked plugin\n\n3. **Verify plugin appears** in the plugin list\n\n## Required Structure\n\nYour plugin directory needs a `plugin.json` manifest file defining metadata and component paths, plus directories for skills, rules, subagents, MCP servers, and hooks as applicable.\n\n## Common Issues\n\nThe guide identifies several failure points:\n\n- **Malformed plugin.json**: \"Even a small error here prevents the plugin from loading\"\n- **Incorrect file paths** in the manifest (use relative paths from plugin root)\n- **File permission problems**, particularly on macOS\n- **Caching issues** requiring full Cursor restarts\n- **Missing required fields** in the configuration\n\nThe symlink approach represents a workaround rather than official support for local development, so expect this workflow to potentially change as Cursor evolves its plugin system.","durationMs":5053,"url":"https://dredyson.com/how-i-solved-the-cursor-2-5-plugins-development-problem-complete-step-by-step-guide-for-local-testing/"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"67f6a643-bc16-4e61-99ae-ff3dd39b25f3","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/alisha/Projects/skills","sessionId":"415c4d06-7225-447d-a197-6c6793576b63","version":"2.1.119","gitBranch":"alisha/cursor-install-bug"}
